    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/dr-noncannulated-f1717-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team-cdrh",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves gradation 1 against a required gradation 2; this shortfall is accepted given the standardized single-condition nature of ASTM F1717 and regulatory precedent. Quantitative output comparison satisfies both E/uval (max 1.63 < 1.96) and percent difference (max 7.9% < 10%) acceptance criteria across all QoIs and both laboratories. Uncertainty quantification has been completed over material and geometric input distributions. The overall evidence package supports medium assurance level for model risk level 3, and the FEA framework is accepted for the stated COU.",
